modules.description: Provides functions to create, check, and serialize partition entries. Works with UUIDs, LBA ranges, and Cstruct buffers for low-level data manipulation. Used to parse and generate disk partition metadata in storage systems.

Handles creation and parsing of GPT headers and partition entries, including checksum validation and layout management. Operates on byte sequences, records, and custom types representing GPT structures. Used to generate bootable disk images and analyze disk partition tables.

Handles low-level disk partition management through UUIDs, LBA ranges, and Cstruct buffers, enabling creation, validation, and serialization of partition entries. Supports direct manipulation of binary data for storage system integration. Examples include parsing partition tables, validating LBA boundaries, and generating serialized partition metadata for disk imaging. Key operations include UUID conversion, buffer alignment, and range checking.
